			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Just replying to an earlier post regarding the damage done by pets.
<br />

<br />
I think that pet damage is very situational, since the DPS for pets is pretty much fixed. Over a fight with a very long duration, pets can achieve much higher damage than the 30-50k quoted in previous posts.
<br />

<br />
For example, reading from the rogue thread posted above, regarding a named in Qvic:
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">We parsed a mage pet at 147 k damage alone on the first named....</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The problem with mage pets, as I see it, lies precisely in our inability of increasing their DPS over short periods of time. Perhaps fixing our Frenzied Burnout ability, or transforming it to have several levels might come some way to compensating for such a lack.
<br />

<br />
I would propose that for the duration of the ability the pets be made to do a lot of damage (say 200 dps). At the end of this burst our pets could then be made to die automatically (no chance to suspend pet allowed), or have much reduced stats for another period of time.
<br />

<br />
This might also allow the warrioris to relax a bit with regards to mage pets taking over their role, which would be likely given a sustained increase in damage output and damage mitigation (implied in any sustained and persistent improvements with our pets).</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
