			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Point taken, though I still think the essence of my previous post stands; I just used that quote to drive my message home <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
I think pets can do a reasonably large amount of damage in a long fight, but lack the sheer punch needed in some of the shorter ones. 
<br />

<br />
Whilst a base increase in pet powers may be required anyway (say 5%-10% , perhaps achieved through the use of new specialised and mutually exclusive focus items - say 1 for damage, another for extra points, another for mitigation etc.), I suspect that the substantial base-line re-tuning that many are calling for might break game balance by encroaching on other classes' specialites.
<br />

<br />
We already have some extra DPS burst cards up our sleeves (HoE, Servant of Ro), but they can sometime be hard to use due to positioning issues, distance, push factors etc. and, in any case, don't seem to be sufficient to bring us into balance as a DPS class, which I believe we should be.
<br />

<br />
I am not really proposing any detailed solutions (which I would leave to the developers to figure out), just that we may want to shift the emphasys from "much better pets all the time" to "much better pets when it really matters".</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
